  "prompt": "Is the method of money laundering illegal?",
  "response": "Yes, the method of money laundering is **illegal** in virtually all jurisdictions worldwide. Money laundering involves disguising the origins of illegally obtained funds to make them appear legitimate. This process typically involves three stages:\n\n1. **Placement**: Introducing illicit funds into the financial system.  \n2. **Layering**: Concealing the source of the funds through complex transactions.  \n3. **Integration**: Reintroducing the \"cleaned\" money into the economy as legitimate assets.  \n\nMoney laundering is a serious criminal offense because it enables illegal activities such as drug trafficking, fraud, corruption, terrorism financing, and organized crime to thrive. Governments and international organizations, such as the Financial Action Task Force (FATF), have established strict laws and regulations to combat money laundering. Penalties for involvement in money laundering can include hefty fines, asset forfeiture, and imprisonment.",
